      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the soup",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt {{butter-unsalted}} of butter in a large saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add {{leek}} of sliced ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "leeks",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp73wmks000084v476zqorr6"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " and the onion with a pinch of salt. Cook gently for 10 to 12 minutes until completely soft but not coloured. Add {{floury-potato}} of diced potato and {{chicken-stock}} of stock. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes until the potato is tender.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blend, sieve, and chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blend until completely smooth. Pass through a fine sieve into a large bowl, pressing gently. Stir in {{double-cream}} of cream. Season with salt and white pepper. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Before serving, check the consistency, the soup thickens as it chills. Thin with a splash of cold stock or cream if needed. Serve in chilled bowls with a swirl of cream and snipped chives.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
